At first the pendulums behave basically identically, but over time they diverge and end up having completely different movements. They key feature of this system is that a double pendulum does not have stable movements like a single pendulum would. Its movements are unpredictable and unstable. In the presence of instability, a small difference between two initial states can amplify with time. \
\
Many kinds of instability are at work in the atmosphere, acting on virtually all spatial scales. For example, shearing instabilities (called \'91Kelvin-Helmholtz Instability\'92) act on scales of meters or less. Such shearing instability occurs when you have large velocity differences within a fluid like water or air. You can see this shearing instability causing chaotic fluid motions in the following experiment of a jet of smoke illuminated by a green laser:\
