In the atmosphere, instabilities at various scales interact with each other. Small-scale weather systems, such as cumulus clouds, can modify the larger scales, such as Rossby waves, and these in turn can strongly influence where and when the cumulus clouds grow. <i>It is the combination of instability and scale interactions that leads to sensitive dependence on initial conditions.</i> \
\
