The system traces out a path that looks like two butterfly wings. The wings are called \'91attractors\'92 because the solution tends to stay close to them, while the rest of the domain is avoided. At a randomly chosen time, the probability of finding the solution near one of the attractors is high. Occasionally the solution jumps from one attractor to the other. These transitions between attractors occur somewhat randomly. Lorenz demonstrated that this simple system exhibits sensitive dependence on initial conditions, analogous to the behavior of the forecasts we saw previously. \
